{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Plan review round 6 disposition (BLOCK remediated): explicitly require process_edit to skip creation_channel and creation_channel_inferred through a named immutable-field frozenset before generic assignment, and added a parent AC plus child proof. Also aligned the legacy handoff: 6fe2 provisional unknown remains eligible for e622 inference; the helper no-ops only for concrete recorded/already-inferred values and is called explicitly at the end of process_create/process_snapshot. Accepted advisories to split schema/type vs runtime-output ACs, make compaction test filters non-overlapping, assign diagnostic trust-boundary docs to e622 with final integration in 568c, and add gen_types const -> Literal support. The create_core transition is independently deployable because every core caller is updated in 6fe2 while the public Python facade supplies the temporary python default to import until e622 overrides it."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784267050079858001,"uuid":"7ba182aa-455e-4595-9c56-63eb5f37c668"}